                        <interp inst="t18370612-name-299" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>ANN PILKINOTON</persName>
                  </hi>, sen. I am the wife of Thomas Pilkington, and the mother of Ann Pilkington. I sent the child out about the middle of March—she came back, crying, without her cloak, and gave the account she has now. <hi rend="smallCaps">MARY ALLAN</hi>. I live with Thomas Child, at the Hayfield public-house, Mile-end. The little girl came to me in March—I gave her a pair of sheets—she came back afterwards with her mother without them—they belong to Mr. Child, and were sent to be washed.</p>
